Jevin RHODES, Appellant,
v.
STATE of Missouri, Respondent. No. ED 105590 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION THREE. Filed: April 17, 2018 Alexandria A. Shah, 1010 Market Street, Suite 1100, Saint Louis, MO. 63101, for appellant. Mary H. Moore, P.O. Box 899, Jefferson City, MO. 65102, for respondent. Before: Gary M. Gaertner, Jr., P.J., Robert M. Clayton III, J., and Angela T. Quigless, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

Antoin Brewer (Movant) appeals the judgment of the motion court denying his motion for post-conviction relief under Missouri Rule of Civil Procedure 24.035 (2016) without an evidentiary hearing. We have reviewed the briefs of the parties and the record on appeal, and we conclude the motion court's decision was not clearly erroneous. An extended opinion would have no precedential value. The parties have been provided with a memorandum for their information only, setting forth the reasons for this order. The decision is affirmed. Mo. R. Civ. P. 84.16(b) (2018).
